[147.377785, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.378044, "o", "   - **Impact**: On resume, previously aggregated totals were overwritten instead of accumulated\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.378079, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.378118, "o", "> "]
[147.378301, "o", "   - **Result**: Final totals were incorrect, only reflecting the last run's data\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.378331, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.378362, "o", "> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.378516, "o", "### 3. **Minor: Checkpoint file not properly flushed**\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.378547, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.378577, "o", "> "]
[147.378806, "o", "   - **Problem**: Checkpoint file opened without context manager, no explicit flush/fsync\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.378837, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.379077, "o", "   - **Impact**: Could lose checkpoint data if process killed before OS flushes buffer\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.379104, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.379134, "o", "> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.379162, "o", "> "]
[147.37919, "o", "## Fixes Applied\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.379216, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.379242, "o", "> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.379269, "o", "> "]
[147.379434, "o", "### Fix 1: Track and save actual line number (records_processed)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.379462, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.379498, "o", "```python\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.379527, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.379557, "o", "# BEFORE:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.379586, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.379687, "o", "def save_checkpoint(batch_num):\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.379718, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.379899, "o", "    json.dump({'last_line': batch_num}, open('.checkpoint', 'w'))\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.379933, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.379961, "o", "> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.379987, "o", "# AFTER:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.380015, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.380128, "o", "def save_checkpoint(records_processed):\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.380158, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.380269, "o", "    with open('.checkpoint', 'w') as f:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.380296, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.380474, "o", "        json.dump({'records_processed': records_processed}, f)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.380501, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.380554, "o", "        f.flush()\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.380573, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.380616, "o", "> "]
[147.380677, "o", "        os.fsync(f.fileno())\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.380706, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.380735, "o", "```\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.380762, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.380795, "o", "\u001b[?2004h"]
[147.380823, "o", "> "]
[147.380975, "o", "### Fix 2: Use INSERT ... ON CONFLICT DO UPDATE to accumulate values\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
[147.381, "o", "\u001b[?2004h> "]
[147.381035, "o", "```python\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
